      "description": "<p>Some special abilities and environmental hazards, such as and the long-term effects of freezing or scorching temperatures, can lead to a special condition called exhaustion.</p><p>If an already exhausted creature suffers another effect that causes exhaustion, its current level of exhaustion increases by 1 rank.</p><p>An effect that removes exhaustion reduces its rank by 1. Finishing a long rest reduces a creature’s exhaustion level by 1, provided that the creature has also ingested some food and drink. When a creature exceeds 10 ranks of exhaustion, they die.</p><p>For every rank of exhaustion, a creature has all of the following statistics are reduced by 1, and for every two ranks of exhaustion a creatures speed is reduced by 5;</p><ul><li><p>Armor Class</p></li><li><p>Ability Checks</p></li><li><p>Skill Checks</p></li><li><p>Saving Throws</p></li><li><p>Attack Rolls</p></li><li><p>Damage Rolls</p></li><li><p>Save DC’s</p></li></ul>",
